results.name: Number of distinct prime factors <= n of binomial(2*n,n).
link: T. D. Noe, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
maple: a := n -> nops(numtheory:-factorset(binomial(2*n,n)) minus select(isprime, {$n+1..2*n})): seq(a(n), n=1..82); # _Peter Luschny_, Oct 31 2015
program: a(n)=my(s); forprime(p=2, n, if(valp(2*n, p)>2*valp(n, p), s++)); s \\ _Charles R Greathouse IV_, May 25 2013
xref: Cf. A067434 (number of prime factors in binomial(2*n,n)), A108954.
